Interface Summary
CriteriaExpression.Operator Operator identifiers
 

Class Summary
AND Used for adding CRITERIA1 AND CRITERIA2 to a statement.
BaseLogicGroup See OR and AND
BetweenCriteria Class BetweenCriteria is a Criteria extension that generates the SQL syntax for a BETWEEN operator in an SQL Where clause.
CriteriaExpression Class CriteriaExpression is Criteria class extension that generates the SQL syntax for a compound logic expression in an SQL Where clause.
InCriteria  
IsNotNullCriteria  
IsNullCriteria  
MatchCriteria  
NoCriteria Class NoCriteria is a Criteria that represents an absent operand in an SQL predicate expression so that one may represent a unary operator (for example, NOT) using a binary operator derived from a BaseLogicGroup).
NOT Class NOT is a BaseLogicGroup extension that generates the SQL syntax for the negation operator in a condition in an SQL Where clause.
OR Used for adding CRITERIA1 OR CRITERIA2 to a statement.
